# **Part 1 — Watches**

---

## **1. Do you wear a watch?**

Yes, I do, although not every single day. I usually wear a smartwatch when I go to university or work on projects because it’s very convenient. Apart from checking the time, I can also read notifications, track my steps, and even monitor my study schedule. I think watches nowadays are not just accessories anymore; they’ve become practical tools that help people manage their daily lives more efficiently.

### **中文：**

是的，我会戴手表，不过不是每天都戴。我通常在去学校或者做项目时会戴智能手表，因为它非常方便。除了看时间之外，我还能查看通知、记录步数，甚至管理学习计划。我觉得现在的手表已经不仅仅是饰品了，它更像是帮助人们高效管理生活的工具。

---

## **2. Have you ever got a watch as a gift?**

Yes, I have. I remember that my parents gave me a watch when I graduated from high school. It wasn’t an extremely expensive one, but it meant a lot to me emotionally. They told me that the watch symbolized the importance of time and responsibility as I entered university. Even now, I still keep it carefully because every time I look at it, it reminds me of that important stage in my life.

### **中文：**

有的。我记得高中毕业时，我父母送给我一块手表。它并不是特别昂贵，但对我来说意义很大。他们告诉我，这块手表象征着进入大学后“时间”和“责任”的重要性。直到现在，我还一直好好保存着它，因为每次看到它，我都会想起人生中那个重要阶段。

---

## **3. Why do some people wear expensive watches?**

I think there are several reasons. First of all, some people genuinely appreciate the craftsmanship and design of luxury watches. High-end watches are often made very carefully and can even be considered works of art. Secondly, for some people, expensive watches are a symbol of social status or success. Especially in business settings, wearing a luxury watch may help create a more professional or confident image. Of course, there are also collectors who see watches as long-term investments.

### **中文：**

我觉得原因有很多。首先，有些人确实欣赏高端手表的工艺和设计。奢侈手表通常制作非常精细，甚至可以被看作艺术品。其次，对一些人来说，昂贵手表也是身份和成功的象征。尤其是在商务场合，佩戴名表可能会让人显得更专业、更自信。当然，也有一些收藏者把手表当作长期投资。

---

## **4. Do you think it is important to wear a watch? Why?**

Personally, I don’t think wearing a watch is absolutely necessary nowadays because smartphones can already do almost everything. However, I still think watches are useful in certain situations. For example, during meetings, exams, or workouts, checking a watch is much more convenient and less distracting than taking out a phone. Besides that, wearing a watch can also reflect a person’s sense of style and attitude toward time management.

### **中文：**

就我个人而言，我觉得现在戴手表并不是绝对必要，因为智能手机已经能完成几乎所有功能。不过，我仍然认为手表在某些场景下很有用。比如开会、考试或者运动时，看手表会比拿出手机更方便，也不容易分心。另外，戴手表也能体现一个人的穿搭风格以及时间管理意识。

---

## **5. Do young people in your country like wearing watches?**

Yes, but I think their preferences have changed compared with older generations. Many young people today prefer smartwatches instead of traditional mechanical watches because they focus more on functionality and technology. For instance, smartwatches can monitor health data, support mobile payments, and connect with phones easily. However, there are still some young people who enjoy classic watches because they think they look elegant and mature.

### **中文：**

喜欢，不过我觉得现在年轻人的偏好和老一辈不太一样。如今很多年轻人更喜欢智能手表，而不是传统机械表，因为他们更重视功能性和科技感。比如智能手表可以监测健康数据、支持移动支付，还能方便地连接手机。不过，仍然有一些年轻人喜欢经典手表，因为他们觉得那样看起来更优雅、更成熟。
